<br>
Haste? C2? <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-banner-long.gif" height=60 width=468 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvulcar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vulcar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/19/01 10:43:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaburn</span><hr size=1> I think it would be cool to have a last resort supernuke.  It would take all of your remaining mana on hand, and blast for 3*mana for damage.  So if you're full mana and have 3000 mana, you do 9000k damage in one shot.  Sure, you'd draw aggro big time, but if your tank goes down, you can make a serious dent before you die too.  Or, perhaps you will take down the bad guy and save the day.<br>
<br>
Downside is you would be completely worthless since you would be out of mana.  <br>
<br>
Nobody would be able to question the power of the wizard then.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unatanmagus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Natan Magus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/19/01 10:50:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaburn</span><hr size=1> 1:3 is not enough, imo.<br>
<br>
This shouldn't skill shouldn't be made overpowereing.<br>
But 1:3 for a die-or-kill shoot is not enough.<br>
<br>
I won't use it. Why? I could do way more damage with 3000 mana and regular spells. I can't imagine at the moment (note, i said at the moment!) a situation where i would use all my mana for a 9000ish nuke.<br>
<br>
It should be something around 20K, 25K maybe.<br>
This would be a 1:6 or 1:7 ratio.<br>
<br>
Well, on the other hand, old world dragons woudl go down with two Wizards casting this spell.<br>
<br>
Dunno...<br>
