<br>
Imagine you're on a raid and the main tank (and I do mean <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> main</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->) goes LD.  You've been nuking and staying inside the aggro line like a good boy, but when that tank fully drops connection, you're going to move from #2 to #1 on the aggro list.  Nuke a couple more times and then manaburn when that guy turns to you.  You're a dead man anyway, make every drop of mana count.  Maybe you won't even die.<br>
<br>
This would also be nice on AoE mobs.  Sometimes you just can't avoid the AoE.  If your party is going down and you haven't unloaded yet and you're going to die to the next AoE, might as well manaburn.  Something like that.<br>
<br>
One-shot kills, maybe.  Yes, all your mana is gone, but the mob died instantly and when a mob dies instantly, its friends don't come for you.  Its pet will fail to aggro and therefore despawn, too.  Three wizards could maybe take out a boss monster's henchmen and no one would have to do any crowd control.  Depends on mana, multiplier, and mob hitpoints of course.<br>
<br>
Also, soloing a mob that casts and hits hard, maybe.  It roots you and comes to knock you senseless.  Sometimes you'll get gate off, sometimes you won't.  Manaburn instead.  Maybe it'll die, maybe it'll turn away.<br>
<br>
I'm sure there are a lot of other good uses for such a skill.  Regardless of the hypotheses, at least I'd never die with unused mana again.<br>
